Short SummaryMore than 1 billion people on earth are lacking access to potable water. High levels of bacteria, other biological and chemical contaminants plague rural water supplies; municipal water, on the other hand, is often contaminated by high levels of chlorine (when treated), lead, chemicals and heavy metals.Also, due to ever-increasing regional scarcity of water (droughts) we will be relying more and more on desalination of sea water for our drinking water.The problem is that desalination is a very expensive process. Its' technology is extremely costly and it uses immense amounts of energy to remove salt from the sea water.Strategic Water Resources, Inc. (SWR) of Mystic, CT SWR was created by a focused team of scientist, engineers and entrepreneurs that possess decades of unique experience and skill sets especially suited to tackling this growing crisis.Our website: www.strategicwaterresources.netSWR has developed a revolutionary technology, the Neptune CF (patent pending), which is unique to the world of water purification; it purifies water through a process we call "Forward Osmosis". What's so exciting about our Neptune CF is that it purifies water - to include desalination - at far lower costs than the traditional method, Reverse Osmosis.In Reverse Osmosis the process of turning sea water into fresh water requires a great deal of energy.  It also needs large scale, specialized equipment whereas our Neptune CF uses far less energy and - the unit designed to produce 50,000 gallons per day -can fit into a 40' shipping container, in which it is housed.It can also be powered by renewable energy.Because SWR's Forward Osmosis System can be built economically on a far smaller scale and uses 80% less electricity than Reverse Osmosis, it could become a real "game changer" in terms of purifying and/or desalinating water economically.Lower costs in turn, will make clean water accessible to far more people than at present.There's also an additional benefit to SWR's Neptune CF:  a high concentration of reactive O1 gas is produced by SWR's proprietary process which, in effect, super oxygenates the purified water it produces. In preliminary trials this super-oxygenated water was shown to increase the rate of plant growth by 30%. Independent verification of these findings by two New England State Agricultural Departments is about to begin.Once we receive these two States' "blessings", SWR will be positioned to provide hydroponic farms oxygen- enriched water supplies that will shorten growth cycle time while enhancing plant nutrient content. As a business we are in our infancy. SWR is less than a year old and is in its' “pre-revenue” phase; as in, we have yet to earn any money.As a result we are seeking your support to help fund the crucial, 2nd phase of our growth.If we were successful in raising $500,000, the following will become realty: We'll be able to cover day-to-day operations in the near term ($50,000) and we'll be able to build a scaled demonstration unit to be used as a precondition to entering the marketplace ($450,000).The private sector has already reacted positively to Strategic Water Resources Neptune CF technology, as illustrated by a Letter of Intent we recently received from a Fortune 500 Company to deliver three desalination plants to locations in Panama, Columbia and the Caribbean.We also have another dozen business deals, pending the construction of the scaled demonstration unit, to include:  Treatment of landfill leachate in Massachusetts;
High oxygen process water for hydroponic greenhouse project; Water treatment plants in Pennsylvania; 
Wastewater treatment for a major seafood processor; etc.Our potential market(s) is a vast one and if the early response from a cross-section of industries to SWR is any indication of what the future may hold then it will be  a very bright one. Provided of course, that we can raise the necessary money to keep going.We are also very much committed to helping the third world overcome its' myriad water problems as soon as we're able. Our lower cost, smaller-scaled water projects, could make the difference between life and death for thousands of destitute people.We thank you for considering our appeal.All the best,The SWR Team
